         "id": "2097ecb4-8f27-4205-8455-dc527e833f88",
         "name": "Indigenous of Piratininga",
         "history": [
            "On this page, we list indigenous people that lived in Piratininga and are descendant of Tibiriçá."
         ],
         "people": [
            {
               "id": "19d7f275-e79b-448f-9ed5-2d904a99e035",
               "name": "Tibiriçá / Martim Afonso",
               "history": [
                  "The first registers about Tibiriçá were made by Pero Lopes de Sousa in his diary. Among the citations we reinforce the relationship with João Ramalho and Piratininga (<htcite0>). In your \"Memórias para a História da Capitania de São Vicente\", Gaspar Madre de Deus names him \"Tebireçá\" and also lists his leadearship positions and his Christian name: <ul> <li><i>\"Senhor dos Campos de Piratininga\"</i> (<htcite1>)</li> <li>His Christian name <i>\"Martim Afonso Tebiriçá\"</i> (<htcite2>)</li> <li>An infant <i>\"Príncipe\"</i> (<htcite3>)</li></ul>",
                  "The relationship between Tibiriçá with the church was excellent, the Priest Saint José de Anchieta informs us that <i>\"nosso principal, grande amigo e protetor Martim Afonso\"</i> (<htcite4>) when Piratininga was under attack, but we cannot hide the wrong vision about American Indigenous few lines after these graceful words when he reports that Tibiriçá has \"... tanta madureza que não parecia homem do Brasil.\"(<htcite5>). In this document, the Priest Saint also reports that Tibiriçá died in the year 1562."
               ],
