      {
         "id": "456d059c-d096-4202-938a-7dbfc9ad42ad",
         "name": "Indigenous of Ururay",
         "history": [
            "On this section it is listed people hat lived near of Ururay when Martim Afonso de Sousa arrived."
         ],
         "people": [
            {
               "id": "9c20653c-d6b8-4ff0-8401-cb1fea80dc17",
               "name": "Piqueroby",
               "history": [
                  "In opposition to his brother, Tibiriçá, that was not aligned with the church and colonizers, Piqueroby made a war against them (<htcite0>), probably, as a side effect of his actions, there is not any documentation citing him explicitly.",
                  "The first reference to his name appears in 17th century through memories of Priest Jorge Moreira (<htcite1>). In the footnotes present in \"Cartas Jesuíticas\", that was published in 1933, the editors showed different personal names to Piqueroby that other authors used (<htcite2>).",
                  "The actions of Piqueroby, and other inhabitants, in the war years are described in works like of Glória Kok (<htcite3>), inside this work, there is a description that his brother-in-law João Ramalho was refusing to obey war orders, he received threat of arrest and exile (<htcite4>; <htcite5>), but the war was not against his brother-in-law, as it was explained by Beatriz Perrone-Moisés and Renato Sztutman, the war moved to opposite sides cousins, and brothers. As a final act, there was a <b>massacre</b> against Indigenous people (<htcite6>)."
               ],
               "parents": [
                  {
